channel.title: Doctor Who End of Time tragedy
channel.description:
This Chapter is actully quite interesting considering the Time Lords return and so does Gallifrey the Planet where all Time Lords lived and where the Time War was interacting in. It returns right on top of the Earth, the Time Lord president was trying to destroy all living things
[b]Well I'm generally pissed. Everything goes well until The Doctor regenerates and I'm pissed because I was in love with David Tennant in a non-homo way. He was the best one in the whole programme. The saddest part is, they replaced him with [url=http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/77/11th_Doctor.jpg/200px-11th_Doctor.jpg]a retard.[/url][/b]
So if you like the Doctor Who series then post here your favourite Doctor and Chapter
Long lived David Tennant, the best Doctor ever.

item.title: Doctor Who End of Time tragedy
item.dc:creator: @TabbyKiller TabbyKiller
item.description:
@TabbyKiller wrote:

You should really get into watching them, they get exciting and really really addictive. But now that there’s a new Doctor… I guess I wont like it as much.

I was hoping the 10th Doctor was the last and it was going to end with him travelling the universe still helping out others from evil until time itself had really ended.

I actually was so pissed I sent a message to Sarah saying

Well honestly David Tennant was the best actor on the Doctor Who Series and I was wondering if David was going to compromise with the Director and see if the 11th Doctor would some how just evolve back in to the 10th Doctor (david tennant) because the 10th doctor is deep down inside the 11th doctor fighting to get out, and in the end does.

I really do not like the fact that David Tennant even considered leaving Doctor Who this time around.

Please reply as fast as you can please and thank you.

Contact either David Tennant or Sarch
